text.tspan: Here, we show an example of how the marker can be printed for a tool with a 8 [mm] diameter.
For a different tool size you can repeat the same equations:
If you want to resize the marker use Inkscape in [mm] settings!
Also, to get a "neon-looking" green we recommend you to buy green sticker paper,
and print the black-and-white version of the marker on that neon-green paper instead:
After getting the right sizes and background color, spread a bunch of markers around this
page, and on Inkscape click on File > Save as.... > .PDF > Save
